org.eclipse.xtend.lib.macro.services

Interface TypeLookup

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    TransformationContext

    @Beta
public interface TypeLookup
    Facilities to lookup Java type declarations generated within the currently processed CompilationUnit.
    Author:
    Sven Efftinge

      • findClass

        MutableClassDeclaration findClass(String qualifiedName)
        Parameters:
        qualifiedName - - the qualified name of the type to look up
        Returns:
        the MutableClassDeclaration with given qualified name, or null if no such class declaration is contained in the currently processed CompilationUnit

      • findTypeGlobally

        Type findTypeGlobally(Class<?> clazz)
        Parameters:
        clazz - - the clazz representing the type to look up
        Returns:
        the type with the same qualified name as the given Class object, or null if that type couldn't be found on the compilation units classpath.

      • findTypeGlobally

        Type findTypeGlobally(String typeName)
        Parameters:
        typeName - - the qualified name of the type to look up
        Returns:
        the type with the given qualified name, or null if such a type couldn't be found on the compilation units classpath.
